Commented on #1308 [CI]: Request Update to DistroAV in NixOS Package

Hmmm, I'm not sure if Qlibrary would help. The problem that patch solves is the fact that NixOS by default has no dynamic library loader available. At it's root, Nix is designed to to make builds repeatable by explicitly linking dependencies during build/install time through the Nix Store so you can have as many variations of a package as you want. Generally we make patches hard-coding dependencies like this because Nix is able to check for differences between packages when you update your system and use a dependency tree to automatically update all dependents of a package when this happens. (ex. if NDI were to update to 6.3, Nix would automatically rebuild DistroAV with the new library path) The only major change that I can think that might make this easier for the NixOS crowd is adding a cmake flag/environment variable that we can set before build to specify that path without needing a patch.
